MarR,MarR_2 Identified by match to protein family PF01047. Regulators with the marR-type HTH domain are present in bacteria and archaea and control a variety of biological functions, including resistance to multiple antibiotics, household disinfectants, organic solvents, oxidative stress agents and regulation of the virulence factor synthesis in pathogens of humans and plants. Many of the marR-like regulators respond to aromatic compounds
